IP Addressing and Network Communication

Today we had a class about IP addressing and how devices talk to each other.
I found out about IPv4 and IPv6 addresses what they look like how they are different and why we needed IPv6 because IPv4 addresses were running out. 
We learned about IP addresses, private IP addresses loopback addresses, subnet masks, default gateways and MAC addresses and the teacher showed us examples to make it clearer.
The teacher showed us how devices find each other on a network and how information gets from one device to another.
I also learned about the Domain Name System, which is called DNS for short.
It helps us use website names instead of IP addresses when we browse the internet.
We tried out some network commands like ping, ipconfig and tracert to see how to test if devices are connected and fix problems.
The teacher explained IP addressing and network communication in a way that was easy to understand. I learned a lot, about IP addressing and network communication.
